<paragraph id="3E7F368EFFEF472FFF2B7878FCFBFCAB" blockId="9.[178,1085,812,864]" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: from central 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFDA77879FDF0FC89" box="[574,632,812,834]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Spain</collectingCountry>
over most of south-western and central Europe, Balkans, 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFEFF781FFE38FCAB" box="[358,432,842,864]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Greece</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFD81781FFDD6FCAB" box="[536,606,842,864]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFDF1781FFD34FCAB" box="[616,700,842,864]" name="Ukraine" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFCBB781FFCE7FCAB" box="[802,879,842,864]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E7F368EFFEF472FFF2B7825FCA9FBDC" blockId="9.[178,1085,879,1047]" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">
R e m a r k s: the main food plant of this species is 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEF472FFD7D783AFC32FC4E" box="[740,954,879,901]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Onobrychis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="938" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viciifolia">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEF472FFD7D783AFC32FC4E" box="[740,954,879,901]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Onobrychis viciifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is an important pest in the root of this fodder crop particularly in Central 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEF472FFCF778D9FC4DFC69" box="[878,965,908,930]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(TAMER &amp; ÖZER 1990). It also occurs in 
<collectingRegion id="FC04F86CFFEF472FFE7378FFFD2DFC74" box="[490,677,937,959]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Erzurum Province</collectingRegion>
and gave damage in this plant particularly in nonirrigated growing areas (GÜLTEKIN &amp; GÜÇLÜ 1997). The authors consider 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEF472FFF2B78B1FD03FC31" authority="GORBUNOV &amp; SPATENKA 2001" authorityName="GORBUNOV &amp; SPATENKA" authorityYear="2001" box="[178,651,996,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mira">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEF472FFF2B78B1FEC4FC31" box="[178,332,996,1018]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Bembecia mira</emphasis>
GORBUNOV &amp; ŠPATENKA 2001
</taxonomicName>
as a new synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEF472FFCF678B1FBB5FC31" baseAuthorityName="SCOPOLI" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[879,1085,996,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scopigera">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEF472FFCF678B1FBB5FC31" box="[879,1085,996,1018]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="938">Bembecia scopigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because no specific discriminating characters could be found.
</paragraph>
